An IterativeBackgroundWorker follows the BackgroundWorker design pattern but instead of running an arbitrary computation it iterates a function a fixed number of times and reports intermediate and final results. The worker is paramaterized by its internal state type.
Percentage progress is based on the iteration number. Cancellation checks are made at each iteration. Implemented via an internal BackgroundWorker.
